Abstract

This volume presents the minimal set of physical laws that govern the universe. Building directly upon the mathematical foundation established in Volume I, we derive the structure of space-time, the motion of bodies, the nature of fields, the principles of thermodynamics, the probabilistic framework of quantum mechanics, and the geometry of relativity. Each equation is selected for its universality and necessity. No historical narrative, no speculative theory, no appendices. Only the axiomatic core of physics as understood by human civilization. This is the second layer of the Civilization Codec—the transformation of pure mathematics into the laws that shape matter, energy, space, and time.

