Chapter 158 — The Measurement Problem

Quantum mechanics has two evolution laws:

· Unitary evolution (Schrödinger equation): deterministic, reversible
· Measurement collapse: probabilistic, irreversible

The transition between them is not described. This is the measurement problem.

Interpretations:

Interpretation Key Idea Status
