Many-Worlds All possibilities realized, branching universes No collapse, but ontology heavy
Bohmian Mechanics Particles have trajectories guided by wavefunction Nonlocal, deterministic
Objective Collapse Spontaneous collapse mechanisms (GRW, Penrose) Testable in principle
QBism Wavefunction represents subjective knowledge Operational, not realist

Key Experimental Tests:

· Collapse models predict slight heating of matter
· Superconducting qubits can test decoherence
· Large molecule interference experiments push quantum-classical boundary

No consensus. The interpretation of quantum mechanics remains open.

